request.description:
Same as 'Get Spending Total by Category' but with `category` omitted: returns a breakdown of totals across every category that had activity in the range, plus a server-computed grand total across all of them. Uncategorized transactions are excluded.

Example response:
```json
{
  "breakdown": [
    { "categoryId": 1, "categoryName": "Groceries", "from": "2026-06-01", "to": "2026-06-30", "totalSpent": 150.32 },
    { "categoryId": 2, "categoryName": "Transport", "from": "2026-06-01", "to": "2026-06-30", "totalSpent": 40.00 }
  ],
  "totalSpent": 190.32
}
```
`totalSpent` is the sum of each breakdown entry's (already absolute-valued) `totalSpent` — i.e. what you'd get adding up the list yourself, computed once server-side.
